al%20level%20of%20interest%20from%20onlookers%20outside%20the%20country%2C%20including%20the%20world's%20richest%20man%20Elon%20Musk%2C%20who%20caused%20an%20outcry%20in%20Germany%20by%20throwing%20his%20weight%20behind%20the%20far-right%20Alternative%20Alice%20Weidel.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20Look%20At%20Top%20Contenders%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOlaf%20Scholz%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%2066-year-old%20centre-left%20Social%20Democrat%20has%20been%20Germany's%20chancellor%20since%20December%202021.%20Seeking%20a%20second%20term%2C%20Scholz%20has%20a%20wealth%20of%20government%20experience%2C%20having%20previously%20served%20as%20Hamburg's%20mayor%20and%20as%20German%20labour%20and%20finance%20minister.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20chancellor%2C%20Scholz%20launched%20an%20effort%20to%20modernize%20Germany's%20military%20after%20Russia's%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%20and%20made%20Germany%20Ukraine's%20second-biggest%20weapons%20supplier.%20His%20government%20prevented%20an%20energy%20crunch%20and%20tried%20to%20counter%20high%20inflation.%20But%20his%20three-party%20coalition%20became%20notorious%20for%20infighting%20and%20collapsed%20in%20November%20as%20it%20argued%20over%20how%20to%20revitalize%20the%20economy%20%E2%80%94%20Europe's%20biggest%2C%20which%20has%20shrunk%20for%20the%20past%20two%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EFriedrich%20Merz%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Germany's%2069-year-old%20opposition%20leader%20has%20emerged%20as%20the%20front-runner%20in%20the%20election%20campaign%2C%20with%20his%20centre-right%20Union%20bloc%20leading%20polls.%20Merz%20became%20the%20leader%20of%20his%20Christian%20Democratic%20Union%20party%20after%20longtime%20Chancellor%20Angela%20Merkel%20%E2%80%94%20a%20former%20rival%20%E2%80%94%20stepped%20down%20in%202021.%20Since%20then%2C%20he%20has%20taken%20the%20party%20in%20a%20more%20conservative%20direction.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20election%20campaign%2C%20Merz%20has%20made%20curbing%20irregular%20migration%20a%20central%20issue.%20However%2C%20he%20lacks%20experience%20in%20government.%20He%20joined%20the%20European%20Parliament%20in%201989%20before%20becoming%20a%20lawmaker%20in%20Germany%20five%20years%20later.%20He%20took%20a%20break%20from%20active%20politics%20for%20several%20years%20after%202009%2C%20practising%20as%20a%20lawyer%20and%20heading%20the%20supervisory%20board%20of%20investment%20manager%20BlackRock's%20German%20branch.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERobert%20Habeck%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%2055-year-old%20Habeck%20is%20the%20candidate%20of%20the%20environmentalist%20Greens.%20He's%20also%20Germany's%20current%20vice%20chancellor%20and%20the%20economy%20and%20climate%20minister%2C%20with%20responsibility%20for%20energy%20issues.%20As%20co-leader%20of%20the%20Greens%20from%202018%20to%202022%2C%20he%20presided%20over%20a%20rise%20in%20the%20party's%20popularity%2C%20but%20in%202021%20he%20stepped%20aside%20to%20let%20Annalena%20Baerbock%20%E2%80%94%20now%20Germany's%20foreign%20minister%20%E2%80%94%20make%20the%20party's%20first%20run%20for%20the%20chancellor's%20job.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHabeck's%20record%20as%20a%20minister%20has%20drawn%20mixed%20reviews%2C%20particularly%20a%20plan%20his%20ministry%20drew%20up%20to%20replace%20fossil-fuel%20heating%20systems%20with%20greener%20alternatives%20that%20deepened%20divisions%20in%20the%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAlice%20Weidel%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%2046-year-old%20Weidel%20is%20making%20the%20first%20bid%20of%20the%20far-right%2C%20anti-immigration%20Alternative%20for%20Germany%2C%20or%20AfD%2C%20for%20the%20country's%20top%20job.%20An%20economist%20by%20training%2C%20Weidel%20joined%20the%20party%20shortly%20after%20it%20was%20founded%20in%202013.%20She%20has%20been%20co-leader%20of%20her%20party's%20parliamentary%20group%20since%20the%20party%20first%20won%20seats%20in%20the%20national%20legislature%20in%202017.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWeidel%20has%20been%20a%20co-leader%20of%20the%20party%20itself%20since%202022%2C%20along%20with%20Tino%20Chrupalla.%20In%20December%2C%20she%20was%20nominated%20as%20the%20candidate%20for%20chancellor%20%E2%80%94%20though%20other%20parties%20say%20they%20won't%20work%20with%20the%20AfD%2C%20so%20she%20has%20no%20realistic%20path%20to%20the%20top%20job%20at%20present.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhen%20Will%20The%20Results%20Come%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20likely%20to%20take%20several%20days%20after%20February%2023%20to%20confirm%20the%20final%20results%20of%20the%20election.%20However%2C%20based%20on%20the%20exit%20polls%2C%20fairly%20reliable%20results%20are%20likely%20to%20be%20out%20by%20Sunday%20evening%2C%20but%20there%20may%20still%20be%20some%20uncertainty%20as%20the%20counting%20of%20votes%20by%20post%20(a%20trend%20which%20is%20on%20the%20rise)%20takes%20time.%20The%20performance%20of%20smaller%20parties%20will%20also%20factor%20in%20result%20timing%20as%20Germany%20has%20a%20norm%20of%20electing%20a%20coalition%20government.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20after%20the%20full%20results%20are%20out%2C%20forming%20a%20new%20government%20will%2C%20most%20likely%2C%20take%20some%20time%20as%20talks%20between%20parties%20on%20coalition%20will%20start%20only%20after%20the%20results.%20The%20coalition%20might%20take%20several%20months%20to%20put%20a%20government%20together.%20It%20depends%20on%20the%20numbers%20at%20play%20and%20the%20political%20arithmetic%20%E2%80%93%20essentially%20the%20extent%20to%20which%20different%20combinations%20of%20parties%20agree%20or%20disagree%20on%20various%20policy%20positions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20Germany%20Forms%20Coalition%20Governments%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20proportional%20voting%20system%20and%20increased%20political%20fracturing%20in%20Germany%20make%20it%20extremely%20difficult%20for%20any%20one%20party%20to%20form%20a%20government%20alone%20and%20a%20coalition%20needs%20to%20be%20formed%20comprising%20parties%20that%20together%20hold%20more%20than%2050%20per%20cent%20of%20the%20seats%20in%20the%20Bundestag%20--%20the%20national%20parliament.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20also%20partly%20political%20culture%20in%20Germany%20to%20prefer%20stable%20majorities%20as%20minority%20governments%20are%20considered%20to%20be%20too%20weak%20and%20unstable.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUntil%20the%20early%201980s%2C%20there%20were%20usually%20three%20parties%20(conservative%2C%20social%20democrats%20and%20liberals)%20in%20Parliament.%20However%2C%20currently%2C%20the%20country%20has%20seven%20parties%20in%20the%20Bundestag.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EParties%20In%20Fray%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGermany%20has%20two%20centrist%2C%20%26quot%3Bbig-tent%26quot%3B%20parties%3A%20Scholz's%20centre-left%20Social%20Democrats%20(SPD)%20and%20the%20opposition%20conservatives%2C%20an%20alliance%20of%20the%20Christian%20Democrats%20(CDU)%20and%20their%20Bavarian%20sister%20party%2C%20the%20Christian%20Social%20Union%20(CSU).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoth%20have%20lost%20support%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20with%20smaller%20parties%20such%20as%20the%20Greens%20and%20far-right%20Alternative%20for%20Germany%20(AfD)%20gaining%20ground.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20SPD%2C%20conservatives%2C%20Greens%20and%20AfD%20are%20all%20fielding%20candidates%20for%20chancellor.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlso%20running%20are%20the%20pro-market%20Free%20Democrats%20(FDP)%2C%20the%20far-left%20Linke%20and%20the%20leftist%20Sahra%20Wagenknecht%20Alliance%20(BSW)%2C%20who%20are%20all%20at%20risk%20of%20missing%20the%205%20per%20cent%20threshold%20to%20make%20it%20into%20parliament%2C%20according%20to%20opinion%20polls.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EPolls%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20conservatives%20have%20been%20leading%20nationwide%20polls%20for%20more%20than%20two%20years%20and%20are%20at%2030%20per%20cent%2C%20according%20to%20the%20latest%20survey%20published%20by%20Forsa%20Institute%20on%20February%2016%2C%20followed%20by%20the%20AfD%20at%2020%20per%20cent.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EScholz's%20SPD%2C%20with%2016%20per%20cent%2C%20has%20dropped%20to%20third%20from%20the%20first%20place%20it%20achieved%20in%20the%202021%20election.%20It%20is%20followed%20by%20the%20Greens%20on%2013%20per%20cent%20and%20Linke%20on%207%20per%20cent.%20The%20FDP%20is%20polling%20at%205%20per%20cent%2C%20with%20the%20BSW%20at%204%20per%20cent%2C%20according%20to%20the%20latest%20poll.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnalysts%20say%20polls%20can%20shift%20quickly%20as%20voters%20are%20less%20loyal%20to%20parties%20than%20they%20once%20were.%20In%20the%202021%20election%20campaign%2C%20the%20conservatives%20went%20from%20frontrunner%20to%20runner-up%20within%20a%20few%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1740032340000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-02%2Ftv257esg_germany-election-afp_625x300_20_February_25.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fgermany-elections-2025-top-candidates-in-race-to-be-next-german-chancellor-7752006%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Germany%20is%20set%20to%20hold%20the%20crucial%20federal%20election%20on%20Sunday%20(February%2023)%20to%20elect%20its%20next%20chancellor.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fgermany-elections-2025-top-candidates-in-race-to-be-next-german-chancellor-7752006%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Kejriwal%20will%20spend%20most%20of%20his%20time%20in%20jail'%3A%20BJP's%20Manjinder%20Singh%20Sirsa%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1740032290000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-118408389%2Cimgsize-38814.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Farvind-kejriwal-will-have-to-spend-most-of-his-time-in-jail-bjps-delhi-minister-pick-manji