%20hanging%20from%20the%20branches%20of%20a%20cherry%20tree.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67afb64aeb4be2fff9a4c4f9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221536%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EEliana%20Vornov%20switched%20jobs%20to%20stay%20remote%20despite%20the%20financial%20downsides.%3Cp%3EKit%20Pulliam%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EWhen%20Eliana%20Vornov's%20job%20announced%20a%20return%20to%20office%2C%20she%20chose%20to%20take%20a%20worse-paying%20remote%20job.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EWhile%20the%20salary%20was%20similar%20to%20her%20previous%20role%2C%20her%20bonus%20and%20stock%20grants%20were%20much%20worse.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20switch%20spurred%20her%20to%20reconsider%20her%20financial%20situation%20and%20become%20more%20active%20in%20managing%20it.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EEliana%20Vornov%2C%20a%20senior%20machine%20learning%20engineer%20based%20out%20of%20Washington%2C%20D.C.%2C%20didn't%20expect%20to%20enjoy%20working%20remotely%20when%20she%20started%20working%20from%20home%20during%20the%20COVID%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20was%20a%20little%20apprehensive%20about%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Vornov.%20%26quot%3BI%20do%20value%20the%20in-person%20energy%20of%20working%20with%20your%20team.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20her%20feelings%20changed%20as%20she%20continued%20to%20work%20remotely.%20When%20her%20old%20employer%20joined%20the%20list%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcompanies-requiring-return-to-office-rto-mandate%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecompanies%20requiring%20a%20return%20to%20the%20office%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20she%20decided%20to%20leave%20her%20company%20of%20eight%20years%20and%20look%20for%20a%20remote%20position%2C%20taking%20a%20financial%20hit%20in%20the%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20doesn't%20regret%20making%20the%20decision%2C%20even%20with%20the%20financial%20drawbacks.%20Here's%20what%20changed%20financially%20when%20she%20changed%20jobs%20to%20continue%20working%20remotely.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2215b8e529-c7d2-4fa8-aa73-e16b85754ca4%5C%22%3EShe%20saved%20hours%20spent%20commuting%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20biggest%20financial%20bonus%20to%20staying%20remote%20is%20the%20time%20and%20money%20she%20has%20saved%20from%20not%20having%20to%20commute.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBefore%20COVID%2C%20I%20was%20commuting%20a%20little%20over%20an%20hour%20each%20way%2C%20every%20day%2C%20and%20that's%20just%20the%20way%20it%20was.%20That's%20what%20you%20do%2C%20that's%20life%20as%20a%20professional%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Vornov.%20%26quot%3BBut%20getting%20that%20time%20back%20has%20been%20incredible.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVornov%20doesn't%20own%20a%20car%2C%20so%20her%20commute%20involved%20walking%20or%20bussing%20to%20a%20metro%20stop%20and%20riding%20the%20metro%20for%2045%20minutes%2C%20assuming%20she%20didn't%20experience%20delays.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEach%20day%2C%20she%20had%20to%20pay%20around%20%2414%20in%20fares%20to%20go%20to%20and%20from%20her%20office.%20If%20she%20had%20been%20paid%20for%20her%20commute%2C%20she%20would%20have%20made%20an%20extra%20%24215%20each%20day%20%E2%80%94%20that's%20over%20%2450%2C000%20of%20unpaid%20travel%20time%20a%20year%2C%20not%20including%20fare%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20didn't%20truly%20understand%20what%20the%20commute%20was%20taking%20from%20my%20life%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Vornov.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20she%20has%20to%20go%20into%20the%20office%20around%20once%20a%20month%2C%20and%20her%20office%20is%20much%20closer%20%E2%80%94%20around%2015%20minutes%20by%20bus%20or%2025%20minutes%20walking.%20Depending%20on%20what%20transit%20method%20she%20uses%2C%20it%20costs%20her%20anywhere%20from%20%240%20to%20%244.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20also%20has%20a%20better%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fwhat-is-401k%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E401(k)%3C%2Fa%3E%2