we%20know%20about%20Ferguson%20and%20his%20priorities%20as%20he%20leads%20the%20commission.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226f19da9d-08e1-4517-b89c-10b910bc3d8c%5C%22%3EFTC%20moves%20under%20Ferguson%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20FTC's%20agenda%20under%20Trump%20is%20just%20getting%20underway%2C%20Alden%20Abbott%2C%20a%20former%20general%20counsel%20of%20the%20Federal%20Trade%20Commission%20who%20is%20familiar%20with%20Ferguson's%20thinking%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20he%20expects%20the%20commission%20under%20Ferguson's%20leadership%20to%20focus%20on%20traditional%20enforcement%20approaches%20at%20the%20agency%20and%2C%20in%20most%20cases%2C%20stop%20pursuing%20former%20chair%20Lina%20Khan's%20expansive%20rulemaking%20arguments%20about%20consumer%20harm%2C%20which%20were%20seen%20by%20some%20as%20pushing%20the%20limits%20of%20established%20antitrust%20legal%20precedent%20and%20drew%20ire%20from%20some%20conservatives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHe's%20smart%2C%26quot%3B%20Abbott%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20he%20views%20himself%20as%20a%20conservative%20lawyer%20who%20believes%20in%20a%20strong%20executive%20reading%20in%20the%20text%20of%20a%20statute%2C%20textualism%2C%20and%20separation%20of%20powers.%20He%20fits%20the%20mold%20of%20the%20elite%20Federalist%20Society%20type%20of%20lawyer.%20So%20I%20think%20you're%20going%20to%20get%20a%20pretty%20aggressive%20FTC%20on%20things%20like%20antitrust%20%E2%80%94%20consumer%20protection%2C%20maybe%2C%20but%20I%20think%20you'll%20you'll%20see%20less%20rulemaking.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20Trump%20took%20office%2C%20the%20FTC%20under%20Ferguson%20has%20moved%20to%20block%20Tempur%20Sealy's%20proposed%20%244%20billion%20acquisition%20of%20Mattress%20Firm%2C%20proposed%20a%20%244.9%20million%20fine%20against%20a%20payment%20processing%20company%2C%20accusing%20it%20of%20deceptive%20business%20practices%2C%20and%20filed%20a%20lawsuit%20against%20the%20three%20largest%20prescription%20drug%20benefit%20managers%20for%20%26quot%3Bengaging%20in%20anticompetitive%20and%20unfair%20rebating%20practices%20that%20have%20artificially%20inflated%20the%20list%20price%20of%20insulin%20drugs%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ftc.gov%2Flegal-library%2Fbrowse%2Fcases-proceedings%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecase%20proceedings%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnder%20his%20tenure%20as%20chair%2C%20Ferguson%20will%20oversee%20the%20illegal%20monopolization%20claims%20against%20four%20major%20US%20tech%20companies%20%E2%80%94%20Google%2C%20Apple%2C%20Amazon%2C%20and%20Meta%20%E2%80%94%20brought%20by%20the%20FTC%20and%20the%20Department%20of%20Justice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAbbott%20said%20he%20expects%20Ferguson%20to%20continue%20pursuing%20these%20cases%2C%20though%20he%20doesn't%20anticipate%20the%20FTC%20under%20his%20leadership%20will%20seek%20major%20breakups%20of%20the%20big%20firms%20as%20potential%20remedies.%20Instead%2C%20Abbott%20said%2C%20he%20expects%20Ferguson%20to%20seek%20policy%20or%20contract%20changes%20to%20remedy%20antitrust%20concerns.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOne%20unknown%20is%20that%20Ferguson%20has%20said%20he's%20concerned%20about%20the%20politicization%20of%20these%20platforms%20and%20concerned%20about%20the%20government%20coercing%20platforms%20or%20working%20with%20platforms%20to%20engage%20in%20political%20censorship%3B%20stuff%20like%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20Abbott%20said.%20%26quot%3BThose%20would%20be%20rather%20novel%20cases%20under%20existing%20antitrust%20laws.%20And%20I%20don't%20know%20how%20he'd%20want%20to%20pursue%20those%2C%20but%20I%20do%20think%20he's%20going%20to%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0he%20said%20he%20wants%20to%20be%20a%20vigorous%20enforcer.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2237893064-1bc5-4920-89a5-d67f94884db4%5C%22%3EKeen%20alignment%20with%20the%20Trump%20administration%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20Trump%20announced%20Ferguson's%20appointment%20as%20chair%20of%20the%20FTC%2C%20Ferguson%20has%20made%20clear%20his%20willingness%20to%20advance%20the%20Trump%20administration's%20priorities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20posts%20on%20X%2C%20Ferguson%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2FAFergusonFTC%2Fstatus%2F1866863372001501516%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epraised%3C%2Fa%3E%20Trump's%20nomination%20of%20Mark%20Meador%20to%20fill%20an%20empty%20commissioner%20seat%20at%20the%20FTC%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2FAFergusonFTC%2Fstatus%2F1867041611323990362%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehighlighted%3C%2Fa%3E%20his%20readiness%20to%20%26quot%3Bimplement%20President%20Trump's%20agenda%26quot%3B%20at%20the%20agency.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cem%3EDo%20you%20work%20for%20the%20FTC%3F%20Contact%20the%20reporter%20with%20tips%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Aktangalakislippert%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Ektangalakislippert%40businessinsider.co%3C%2Fu%3Em%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EShortly%20after%20Trump's%20inauguration%2C%20Ferguson%20announced%20that%20the%20FTC%2C%20under%20his%20leadership%2C%20would%20enthusiastically%20comply%20with%20Trump's%20order%20to%20eliminate%20diversity%2C%20equity%2C%20and%20inclusion%20initiatives%20in%20government%20offices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDEI%20is%20a%20scourge%20on%20our%20institutions%2C%26quot%3B%20Ferguson%20said%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2FAFergusonFTC%2Fstatus%2F1882224298347090228%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epost%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20X%20in%20late%20January.%20%26quot%3BPresident%20Trump%20promised%20the%20American%20people%20that%20he%20would%20end%20it.%20He%20has%20done%20so%20in%20three%20amazing%20executive%20orders.%20Under%20my%20leadership%2C%20the%20FTC%20is%20doing%20its%20part%20to%20end%20the%20DEI%20plague.%20We%20are%20done%20with%20DEI%20at%20the%20FTC.%20No%20DEI%20office%2C%20no%20DEI%20influence%20on%20hiring%2C%20no%20DEI%20programming.%20It%20is%20over.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFerguson%20led%20the%20FTC%20in%20closing%20the%20commission's%20DEI%20office%2C%20placing%20all%20employees%20within%20that%20office%20on%20administrative%20leave%2C%20and%20removing%20materials%20promising%20DEI%20on%20the%20commission's%20website.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20ordered%20a%20review%20of%20all%20FTC%20contracts%2C%20an%20internal%20audit%20of%20the%20commission's%20office%2C%20and%20a%20review%20of%20previous%20commission%20orders%20%26quot%3Bto%20ensure%20that%20the%20Biden%20Administration's%20DEI%20dictates%20did%20not%20make%20their%20way%20into%20formal%20Commission%20decisions%2C%26quot%3B%20an%20FTC%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ftc.gov%2Fnews-events%2Fnews%2Fpress-releases%2F2025%2F01%2Fftc-chairman-ferguson-announces-dei-over-ftc%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epress%20release%3C%2Fa%3E%20related%20to%20the%20decision%20read.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFerguson's%20alignment%20with%20Trump%20has%20already%20ruffled%20the%20feathers%20of%20the%20democrat%20appointee%20on%20the%20commission.%20Commissioner%20Alvaro%20M.%20Bedoya%2C%20another%20Biden%20nominee%2C%20dissented%20from%20Ferguson's%20anti-DEI%20initiative%20with%20a%20statement%20that%20criticized%20Ferguson's%20first%20official%20move%20as%20chair%2C%20reading%3A%20%26quot%3BChairman%20Ferguson%20could%20have%20done%20any%20number%20of%20things%20to%20actually%20lower%20the%20cost%20of%20living%20and%20create%20opportunities%20for%20American%20businesses%20and%20workers.%20He%20did%20none%20of%20them.%20Instead%2C%20he%20cancelled%20'DEI.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22afe8c338-0ffe-40b4-a52d-50f19a459d89%5C%22%3EFormer%20Supreme%20Court%20clerk%20turned%20solicitor%20general%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20his%20FTC%20biography%2C%20the%20Virginia%20native%20earned%20his%20undergraduate%20degree%20and%20law%20degrees%20from%20the%20University%20of%20Virginia%2C%20one%20of%20the%20top%2010%20law%2