%20two%20TikTok%20employees%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EReturn-to-office%20mandates%20have%20become%20a%20hot-button%20issue%20across%20the%20tech%20industry.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcategory%2Ftiktok%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETikTok%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20tightening%20the%20reins%20on%20office%20attendance%2C%20and%20it's%20caught%20some%20employees%20off%20guard.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20plans%20to%20track%20how%20long%20its%20US%20e-commerce%20employees%20are%20in%20the%20office%2C%20requiring%20eight%20hours%20a%20day%2C%20five%20days%20a%20week%2C%20two%20staffers%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20also%20asking%20its%20e-commerce%20organization%2C%20which%20runs%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-tiktok-shop-is-changing-e-commerce%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETikTok%20Shop%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20to%20be%20at%20work%20between%204%20and%207%20p.m.%20PT%2C%20according%20to%20the%20employees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20internal%20messaging%20around%20the%20change%20seemed%20to%20have%20been%20tailored%20to%20TikTok%20and%20ByteDance%20workers%20in%20the%20company's%20Seattle%20office%2C%20where%20much%20of%20the%20e-commerce%20organization%20sits.%20But%20the%20message%20was%20shared%20with%20e-commerce%20employees%20across%20the%20US%2C%20meaning%20East%20Coast%20employees%20could%20end%20up%20working%20as%20late%20as%2010%20p.m.%20to%20comply%2C%20the%20staffers%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETikTok's%20owner%2C%20ByteDance%2C%20is%20based%20in%20China.%20Employees%20previously%20told%20BI%20that%20the%20company%20required%20some%20US%20employees%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftiktok-employees-say-staff-in-china-make-many-product-decisions-2021-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejoin%20calls%20at%20late%20hours%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20accommodate%20different%20time%20zones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20two%20staffers%20said%20they%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftiktok-tracking-employees-return-to-office-surveillance-tool-myrto-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eexpected%20to%20be%20tracked%3C%2Fa%3E%20each%20time%20they%20used%20their%20badge%20to%20enter%20or%20leave%20office%20buildings%20to%20keep%20tabs%20on%20their%20hours.%20The%20employees%20spoke%20on%20the%20condition%20of%20anonymity%20because%20they%20were%20not%20authorized%20to%20discuss%20the%20policy%20change.%20Their%20identities%20are%20known%20to%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETikTok%20declined%20to%20comment%20on%20the%20policy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20return-to-office%2C%20or%20RTO%2C%20move%20specifically%20affects%20employees%20who%20work%20on%20e-commerce%2C%20not%20others%20within%20the%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETikTok%20Shop%20is%20a%20priority%20at%20the%20company%2C%20which%20has%20sought%20to%20gain%20market%20share%20in%20an%20e-commerce%20ecosystem%20dominated%20by%20players%20like%20Amazon%20and%20Shopify.%20It's%20grown%20quickly%20since%20launching%20in%20the%20US%20in%20November%202023%2C%20last%20year%20pulling%20in%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftiktok-drove-100-million-in-us-black-friday-sales-livestream-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E%24100%20million%20in%20US%20sales%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Black%20Friday%20alone.%20By%20some%20measures%2C%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftiktok-shop-better-at-keeping-customers-than-temu-shein-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Erepeat%20purchases%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20it%20beat%20retailers%20like%20Walmart.%20But%20the%20company%20has%20a%20long%20road%20ahead.%20It%20could%20be%20using%20RTO%20mandates%20to%20try%20to%20drive%20up%20performance%2C%20as%20other%20tech%20companies%20have.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20TikTok's%20e-commerce%20team%20was%20previously%20required%20to%20